### The "No-Python" Playbook (`deploy_vbox.yml`)

Replace your current playbook content with this. This version uses only the `raw` module to move the file and set up the service.

```yaml
---
- name: Emergency Deployment (Bypassing Python Errors)
  hosts: vbox_vms
  gather_facts: no
  become: yes

  tasks:
    - name: Install Java via Raw
      raw: apt-get update && apt-get install -y openjdk-17-jdk

    - name: Create directory via Raw
      raw: mkdir -p /opt/copiloton && chown ansibleadmin:ansibleadmin /opt/copiloton

    - name: Transfer JAR (Using SCP directly)
      # Since 'copy' is failing due to Python, we use a local shell command to SCP it
      local_action: shell scp -P 2222 ./target/onsathwiklearning-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar ansibleadmin@127.0.0.1:/opt/copiloton/app.jar
      become: no

    - name: Create Systemd Service via Raw
      raw: |
        printf "[Unit]\nDescription=Copiloton Java Service\nAfter=network.target\n\n[Service]\nUser=ansibleadmin\nExecStart=/usr/bin/java -jar /opt/copiloton/app.jar\nRestart=always\n\n[Install]\nWantedBy=multi-user.target" > /etc/systemd/system/copiloton.service

    - name: Start Service via Raw
      raw: systemctl daemon-reload && systemctl enable copiloton && systemctl restart copiloton

```

